`fromTransition(reducer, initialState)` gives you a first-class actor that isn't a full state machine — just a pure `(state, event) => nextState` reducer. It still plugs into the XState actor system: you register it under `setup.actors`, `invoke` it by id, and subscribe to its snapshot. This is the right shape for small state buckets (counters, lists, form scratchpads) where a whole machine would be overkill.

