A compound state in XState v5 declares `initial` plus a `states` map, so it is itself a mini state machine. Transitions on the parent apply to every child; transitions inside a child only fire while that child is active. Absolute targets use `#machine-id.path`, relative targets use the child name, and `.sibling` targets a sibling under the same parent.

```ts
