In XState v5, an `on` handler can be an array of transition objects. The runtime evaluates each entry top-to-bottom: the first whose `guard` passes is taken. Guards are declared by name in `setup({ guards })` and receive `({ context, event })`. Unguarded entries at the end act as fallbacks and always match.

